qas.question: What island did Great Britain lose in 1756?

answers.text: Great Britain lost Minorca in the Mediterranean to the French in 1756

qas.question: What possession did the French lose to the Brits in 1758

answers.text: captured the French colonies in Senegal in 1758

qas.question: Identify the French colonies lost  to the British in 1759 and 1762.

answers.text: The British Royal Navy took the French sugar colonies of Guadeloupe in 1759 and Martinique in 1762

qas.question: What success did the British have in Cuba?

answers.text: Spanish cities of Havana in Cuba
